$ VBA: variables

A variable has a → development/languages/VBA/language/datatypes[datatype].

Local variables are declared with the → development/languages/VBA/language/statements/dim[`dim`] statement, global variables with
→ development/languages/VBA/language/statements/public[`public`].

The address in memory where the value of a variable is stored is returned with the function → development/languages/VBA/functions/xPtr[`varPtr(var)`].

{ Scope

  There are five scopes (aka *extents*) for variables
    • Program: variable is defined by *host application* or *VBA specification*
    • Module: which also include *static local variables* within a → development/languages/VBA/language/subs-and-functions[sub or function].
    • Sub/function
    • → development/languages/VBA/language/datatypes/object[Object] (member variables)
    • Aggregate: in → development/languages/VBA/language/datatypes/user-defined[UDTs]

}

sa:
  → development/languages/VBA/language/null-and-nothing-etc[Null and nothing etc.]
